If we had 3 stats for a game - Might / Agility  / Lex - and each of them only gated equipment, what achetypes would each of those things build into? 


Might would probably just be raw BIG NOMBER and HP tanking. 

Agility would probably be +AP (maybe specialized types of AP to avoid ridiculousness) and dodge / trap tanking.

Lex would be... an additional resource that is then converted into extra riders and other effects. Not like stars from the Regent; since it isn't part of a kit it can't gate card play. Probably more like mana from Slice & Dice, where you've got a limited selection of spells and the ever-present Burst, and you spend energy generated every turn to apply the spell to the thing you do. 



 - A baseline number for attacks should probably be 3 if we're using a GH style modifier deck. Makes the modifiers all very impactful.
 - With a baseline number of 3 for attacks, to get the feeling of Diablo in there, Forgiven should have 1 HP. 
 

